15/10/2003
ANKARA, Turkey -- Turkey assumes command of the ground element of the NATO Response Force (NRF) on Wednesday (15 October). 
The mandate will last until the summer of 2004 and will include units and personnel from Belgium, the Czech Republic, France, Greece, Hungary, Italy, Norway and Spain. 
A Turkish general will also be in command of the NATO Brigade, set up as part of the founding stage of the NRF. 
The force will achieve full operational capability, with 21,000 troops, by fall 2006. 
(Anadolu Agency, SHAPE - 14/10/03)
